'''消耗战'''（{{Lang-en|war of attrition}}），又称'''摩擦战'''、'''持久战'''，是一种加入了时间因素的[[博弈|博弈]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://econtheory.org/ojs/index.php/te/article/viewFile/20190849/24484/709|title=An N-person war of attrition with the possibility of a noncompromising type|publisher=Gakushuin University|date=2019年|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828201647/https://econtheory.org/ojs/index.php/te/article/viewFile/20190849/24484/709|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfu.ca/econ-research/RePEc/sfu/sfudps/dp17-10.pdf|title=War and Conflict in Economics: Theories, Applications, and Recent Trends|publisher=Simon Fraser University|date=2017年7月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828201734/http://www.sfu.ca/econ-research/RePEc/sfu/sfudps/dp17-10.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mcafee.cc/Papers/PDF/Warold.pdf|title=Continuing Wars of Attrition|publisher=University of Texas|date=2000年6月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828201836/https://www.mcafee.cc/Papers/PDF/Warold.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.econstor.eu/bitstream/10419/25707/1/560544278.PDF|title=Less fighting than expected: experiments with wars of attrition and all-pay auctions|publisher=Jena Economic Research Papers|date=2007年12月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828200848/https://www.econstor.eu/bitstream/10419/25707/1/560544278.PDF|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://neumann.hec.ca/pages/nicolas.sahuguet/warofattrition.pdf|title=A war of attrition with endogenous effort levels|publisher=Yale University 及 HEC Montréal|date=2008年10月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110427234530/http://neumann.hec.ca/pages/nicolas.sahuguet/warofattrition.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref> 在摩擦战中，两名参与者会为了一定的[[利益|利益]]而进行斗争，他们中最先放弃的将会一无所有，坚持到最后的则会获得战利品，如果同时放弃则统统什么都得不到。但是随着[[时间|时间]]的进行，双方都得为继续斗争而付出额外的代价。当其中一方在第一回合就放弃，而对方选择斗争时可构成[[纳什均衡|纳什均衡]]。<ref>{{lang|en|[http://theincidentaleconomist.com/analysis-of-war-of-attrition-game/ Analysis of the “War of Attrition” Game]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.princeton.edu/sites/default/files/germang/files/war_of_attrition.pdf|title=Wars of Attrition with Evolving Payoffs|publisher=Princeton University|date=2019年6月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828192949/https://scholar.princeton.edu/sites/default/files/germang/files/war_of_attrition.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nuffield.ox.ac.uk/economics/papers/1998/w1/attrwebb.pdf|title=The Generalized War of Attrition|publisher=Stanford University|date=1997年11月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210426144759/http://www.nuffield.ox.ac.uk/economics/papers/1998/w1/attrwebb.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.waseda.jp/fpse/winpec/assets/uploads/2015/02/No.E1420Yasushi-Asako.pdf|title=One-sided Games in a War of Attrition|publisher=Waseda University|date=2015年2月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505211654/https://www.waseda.jp/fpse/winpec/assets/uploads/2015/02/No.E1420Yasushi-Asako.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ftp.iza.org/dp11595.pdf|title=Voting as a War of Attrition|publisher=IZA Institute of Labor Economics|date=2018年6月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828193742/http://ftp.iza.org/dp11595.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.socscistaff.bham.ac.uk/rowat/112/final/woa-name.pdf|title=Equilibria in the War of Attrition|author=Neel Radhakrishnan|date=2011年12月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828193834/http://www.socscistaff.bham.ac.uk/rowat/112/final/woa-name.pdf|archivedate=2021|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kellogg.northwestern.edu/faculty/georgiadis/WarOfAttrition.pdf|title=The Absence of Attrition in a War of Attrition under Complete Information|publisher=Northwestern University|date=2021年6月|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org